      "content": "For projecting authority in a high-end international business setting, the standard is classic, conservative tailoring. Think dark, well-fitted suits—navy or charcoal are universally accepted and look sharp. Accessories should be minimal but high quality, like a nice watch and polished shoes. Ultimately, the look needs to scream \"competent\" and \"unflappable,\" which usually means sticking to traditional, well-maintained Western business attire.",
