      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you're in Lagos or Mumbai, you can certainly wear local attire, but it needs to be impeccably tailored and expensive-looking to convey seriousness. In Tokyo, while suits are common, a very high-quality, understated local business wear can signal deep respect for the culture. The key isn't just the garment, but the *quality* and the *confidence* with which you wear it; a poorly fitting local outfit looks like a costume, while a perfect one looks like power.",
